HEADWORD: Medicinal
<hw>Me*dic"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>medicinalis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧dicinal</ets>. See
<er>Medicine</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having curative or palliative
properties; used for the cure or alleviation of bodily disorders;
<as>as, <ex>medicinal</ex> tinctures, plants, or springs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drop tears as fast as the Arabian trees⟦br⟧
Their <qex>medicinal</qex> gum.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to medicine; medical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Medicinally</ent>⟦br⟧
